cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is about adversarial examples in neural machine translation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning models, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper proposes novel attacks using string-edit operations, which could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for character-level NMT, which could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses adversarial training, which is a technique used in neural networks and falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
